WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:03:19.958 --> 00:03:22.958
Cheers!

3
00:03:31.083 --> 00:03:32.333
Excellent.

4
00:03:32.875 --> 00:03:35.541
Let's drink until we drop.

5
00:03:35.750 --> 00:03:37.500
-You should save your energy for tonight.
-Mix it.

6
00:03:37.666 --> 00:03:40.250
Are you kidding me. Tun?
Don't you know who I am?

7
00:03:41.041 --> 00:03:43.250
Alcohol energizes me.

8
00:03:43.708 --> 00:03:46.208
The later it gets. the hornier I become.

9
00:03:46.625 --> 00:03:47.583
-Horny?
-Come. come.

10
00:03:47.958 --> 00:03:50.541
-Let's toast.
-Here's another glass. Have a little sip.

11
00:03:53.666 --> 00:03:55.458
So. tell me. Jane.

12
00:03:56.208 --> 00:03:57.250
What year are you in?

13
00:03:57.958 --> 00:03:58.833
I'm in my fourth year.

14
00:03:58.916 --> 00:04:00.958
You're old enough to do what you want now.

15
00:04:01.375 --> 00:04:03.958
So. how did you meet Tun?

16
00:04:04.333 --> 00:04:05.541
Because he's a hunk.

17
00:04:06.583 --> 00:04:08.625
You keep saying that since college.

18
00:04:08.958 --> 00:04:11.791
Jim had to ask for her number for you.

19
00:04:11.875 --> 00:04:15.958
-you pain in the ass.
-Speaking of college. do you remember

20
00:04:16.333 --> 00:04:17.583
when you got your heart broken?

21
00:04:17.666 --> 00:04:20.916
-He was so drunk.
-Which girl left him a drunken mess?

22
00:04:21.000 --> 00:04:23.458
-Her name was Kay. I do remember that.
-It's "Teochew" Kay.

23
00:04:23.541 --> 00:04:26.208
-Ignore them.
-Right. What do you mean by "ignore them"?

24
00:04:26.833 --> 00:04:29.375
-Wait. I have a question.
-What?

25
00:04:29.458 --> 00:04:31.000
How can a guy like you get married?

26
00:04:31.083 --> 00:04:32.958
Why can't a guy like me get married?

27
00:04:33.750 --> 00:04:36.375
After a long tiring day at work.

28
00:04:36.875 --> 00:04:38.375
all I want is to head home

29
00:04:38.791 --> 00:04:41.208
to cuddle with my wife or my dog.

30
00:04:41.291 --> 00:04:42.958
not waste my life.

31
00:04:43.541 --> 00:04:48.208
-partying with you losers. okay?
-I have nothing to do with this. man.

32
00:04:48.291 --> 00:04:49.625
A good man...

33
00:04:49.958 --> 00:04:52.583
went whoring with me last night.

34
00:04:54.541 --> 00:04:55.750
Fooling around so soon?

35
00:04:57.208 --> 00:04:58.458
Here she comes.

36
00:05:01.208 --> 00:05:02.166
Quiet.

37
00:05:02.291 --> 00:05:03.791
What's so funny?

38
00:05:05.125 --> 00:05:06.416
Nothing. dear.

39
00:05:06.750 --> 00:05:08.958
I have one last thing to say to you.

40
00:05:09.666 --> 00:05:11.416
One more glass!

41
00:05:31.416 --> 00:05:33.083
What are we listening to?

42
00:05:35.125 --> 00:05:36.958
Hey. Don't turn it off.

43
00:05:37.041 --> 00:05:38.250
It's beautiful.

44
00:05:40.958 --> 00:05:42.625
You guys seem tight.

45
00:05:42.875 --> 00:05:44.875
How long has it been
since you last saw each other?

46
00:05:48.583 --> 00:05:49.750
What are you looking at?

47
00:05:50.750 --> 00:05:51.916
Someone beautiful.

48
00:05:54.458 --> 00:05:56.041
That's so sappy.

49
00:06:39.916 --> 00:06:40.916
Are you okay?

50
00:06:43.125 --> 00:06:43.958
Tun.

51
00:06:45.291 --> 00:06:46.458
Is she dead?

52
00:06:55.750 --> 00:06:56.666
Jane. wait!

53
00:07:06.958 --> 00:07:07.875
Just drive away.

54
00:07:09.208 --> 00:07:10.375
I said drive away!

55
00:07:11.958 --> 00:07:13.125
Drive away!

56
00:07:24.125 --> 00:07:25.750
Get closer. please.

57
00:07:26.333 --> 00:07:27.500
Okay.

58
00:07:28.500 --> 00:07:29.916
Big smile. Nuch.

59
00:07:30.666 --> 00:07:32.291
Or you won't look pretty.

60
00:07:40.750 --> 00:07:42.750
All Science graduates.

61
00:07:42.833 --> 00:07:44.875
please gather on the stand
for a class photo.

62
00:07:45.500 --> 00:07:46.833
They're calling you.

63
00:07:47.666 --> 00:07:49.041
Where's Jane?

64
00:07:50.583 --> 00:07:53.083
She's probably taking photos
with her friends.

65
00:07:54.125 --> 00:07:56.708
I thought you guys broke up.

66
00:07:57.416 --> 00:07:59.083
Come on. Let's go.

67
00:08:56.625 --> 00:08:58.791
I called you so many times today
but you didn't pick up.

68
00:08:59.250 --> 00:09:00.625
Was your phone on silent?

69
00:09:00.708 --> 00:09:01.583
No. it wasn't.

70
00:09:09.791 --> 00:09:11.666
Nuch asked about you today.

71
00:09:14.666 --> 00:09:17.041
When will you be free?

72
00:09:17.125 --> 00:09:18.958
She said she wants to...

73
00:09:41.333 --> 00:09:42.166
Jane.

74
00:09:44.416 --> 00:09:46.250
How can you act like this?

75
00:09:50.000 --> 00:09:52.041
You're pretending like nothing happened.

76
00:09:54.375 --> 00:09:55.708
Since that night.

77
00:09:55.791 --> 00:09:57.166
I haven't been able to sleep at all.

78
00:09:59.916 --> 00:10:01.500
Well...

79
00:10:01.583 --> 00:10:03.500
You think it doesn't bother me?

80
00:10:05.500 --> 00:10:07.958
We should have gone out
and checked how she was.

81
00:10:10.041 --> 00:10:11.916
It was an accident. Jane.

82
00:10:13.500 --> 00:10:15.083
That's easy for you to say.

83
00:10:16.708 --> 00:10:18.791
You were not the one behind the wheel.

84
00:10:31.208 --> 00:10:32.875
-Hi. Ti.
-Hey.

85
00:10:33.208 --> 00:10:34.958
How's business?
Have you got a lot of customers?

86
00:10:35.666 --> 00:10:37.500
With you here this early.

87
00:10:38.083 --> 00:10:40.041
I don't think
many customers will be coming.

88
00:10:41.916 --> 00:10:43.416
Are my prints ready?

89
00:10:44.541 --> 00:10:46.500
Yes. Just a second.

90
00:10:51.708 --> 00:10:52.541
Here.

91
00:11:16.958 --> 00:11:18.291
Is your processor broken?

92
00:11:19.875 --> 00:11:20.833
Let me see.

93
00:11:26.416 --> 00:11:27.250
You punk.

94
00:11:27.458 --> 00:11:29.125
If the prints turn out nice.
you get the credit.

95
00:11:29.750 --> 00:11:31.625
If they suck. it's my fault.

96
00:11:32.291 --> 00:11:33.666
Just look at the negatives.

97
00:11:34.583 --> 00:11:36.041
This is impossible.

98
00:11:36.125 --> 00:11:37.791
I took them. I should know.

99
00:11:37.875 --> 00:11:38.875
We'll see.

100
00:11:41.166 --> 00:11:42.250
See?

101
00:11:43.750 --> 00:11:45.541
It's your fault your negatives are ruined.

102
00:12:09.750 --> 00:12:10.583
Tun.

103
00:12:21.750 --> 00:12:22.583
Tun.

104
00:12:40.625 --> 00:12:41.541
Tun.

105
00:12:43.958 --> 00:12:45.041
Can you hear me?

106
00:14:54.250 --> 00:14:55.208
Help!

107
00:14:56.666 --> 00:14:58.083
Help!

108
00:15:32.416 --> 00:15:34.583
Don't be scared. I'm here now.

109
00:15:55.583 --> 00:15:57.041
What's wrong with your camera?

110
00:15:58.458 --> 00:15:59.333
I don't know.

111
00:15:59.625 --> 00:16:01.166
The whole roll is ruined.

112
00:16:03.958 --> 00:16:05.583
That many?

113
00:16:11.708 --> 00:16:13.125
What are these shadows?

114
00:16:14.083 --> 00:16:16.041
My camera must be broken.

115
00:16:18.125 --> 00:16:20.166
I don't know how I'm going to tell Nuch.

116
00:16:24.166 --> 00:16:25.125
Tun.

117
00:16:27.083 --> 00:16:28.500
Look at this picture.

118
00:16:39.958 --> 00:16:41.166
That woman...

119
00:16:42.500 --> 00:16:43.958
Do you think she's dead?

120
00:16:44.666 --> 00:16:46.000
That's enough. Jane.

121
00:16:51.333 --> 00:16:54.166
I'll have my camera fixed tomorrow.

122
00:17:58.708 --> 00:17:59.625
Tun.

123
00:17:59.708 --> 00:18:00.833
Look at this picture.

124
00:18:25.958 --> 00:18:27.625
Are you sure it was here?

125
00:18:35.291 --> 00:18:36.166
Excuse me.

126
00:18:36.291 --> 00:18:37.416
What happened?

127
00:18:39.000 --> 00:18:41.458
A few days ago.
a car ran into the billboard.

128
00:18:41.541 --> 00:18:42.958
The driver must have been drunk.

129
00:18:45.125 --> 00:18:47.041
Was anyone hurt?

130
00:18:48.250 --> 00:18:49.250
No.

131
00:18:50.041 --> 00:18:51.250
Just the broken sign.

132
00:18:51.375 --> 00:18:52.708
Are you sure?

133
00:18:53.250 --> 00:18:54.291
What?

134
00:18:54.458 --> 00:18:55.625
Well...

135
00:18:56.041 --> 00:18:57.250
Nothing. bro.

136
00:18:58.708 --> 00:18:59.791
Thank you.

137
00:19:01.916 --> 00:19:02.875
What?

138
00:19:05.333 --> 00:19:07.875
Are you sure you checked everywhere?

139
00:19:11.458 --> 00:19:12.291
It's nothing.

140
00:19:13.333 --> 00:19:14.791
Thanks. anyway.

141
00:19:19.708 --> 00:19:22.041
My friend called every police station
and hospital around the area.

142
00:19:23.708 --> 00:19:27.166
He said there was no report
of any accidents that night.

143
00:19:27.833 --> 00:19:29.375
How is that possible?

144
00:19:30.458 --> 00:19:32.291
What about the girl we ran over?

145
00:19:33.958 --> 00:19:36.375
Are you sure he called everywhere?

146
00:19:36.708 --> 00:19:38.625
Maybe someone helped her.

147
00:19:39.458 --> 00:19:41.000
Maybe she's fine.

148
00:19:41.083 --> 00:19:42.791
How can she be fine?

149
00:19:42.875 --> 00:19:44.875
We plowed into her like that.

150
00:19:47.750 --> 00:19:49.791
And even if she's fine...

151
00:19:51.291 --> 00:19:53.000
then what's in those photos?

152
00:19:53.625 --> 00:19:56.250
I told you they're not related to her.

153
00:19:56.791 --> 00:19:58.208
They're just bad exposures.

154
00:19:58.291 --> 00:19:59.333
Don't you get it?

155
00:21:03.625 --> 00:21:04.458
Tun.

156
00:21:05.333 --> 00:21:07.000
I think you need to make merit. man.

157
00:21:08.416 --> 00:21:09.500
These pictures...

158
00:21:10.166 --> 00:21:12.583
show that there's a spirit haunting you.

159
00:21:18.916 --> 00:21:21.583
How long have you been
a photographer. you punk?

160
00:21:21.666 --> 00:21:23.458
Why are you showing me these?

161
00:21:23.625 --> 00:21:24.791
I know. but...

162
00:21:25.291 --> 00:21:27.833
Don't you find these shadows strange?

163
00:21:29.958 --> 00:21:31.666
You want to see spirits?

164
00:21:32.375 --> 00:21:33.750
I'll show you something.

165
00:21:42.041 --> 00:21:42.875
Here.

166
00:21:43.666 --> 00:21:44.791
This is Auntie Cham's spirit.

167
00:21:45.791 --> 00:21:47.208
Do you know where she is now?

168
00:21:50.250 --> 00:21:53.125
She's still selling fried bananas
in the next alley.

169
00:21:54.875 --> 00:21:56.500
Here's Auntie Cham. And here.

170
00:21:57.166 --> 00:21:58.208
Those are all Auntie Cham.

171
00:21:58.666 --> 00:22:00.083
They were all taken on the same day.

172
00:22:00.333 --> 00:22:02.166
They're just double exposures.

173
00:22:02.250 --> 00:22:03.458
and out of focus.

174
00:22:04.375 --> 00:22:07.541
Come on. I know that.

175
00:22:15.791 --> 00:22:18.250
Everyone is probably familiar
with this place.

176
00:22:19.625 --> 00:22:22.125
It's just an ordinary location...

177
00:22:23.458 --> 00:22:24.750
that we pass by...

178
00:22:25.583 --> 00:22:27.333
and see every day.

179
00:22:33.166 --> 00:22:35.000
Now look at these pictures.

180
00:22:39.125 --> 00:22:42.125
These are pictures of the same location.

181
00:22:42.916 --> 00:22:44.041
But do you see...

182
00:22:45.416 --> 00:22:47.125
that everything looks better?

183
00:22:49.416 --> 00:22:52.458
That means photography

184
00:22:52.875 --> 00:22:55.208
does not always convey reality.

185
00:22:57.916 --> 00:22:59.416
It depends on how...

186
00:23:00.416 --> 00:23:03.125
the image is framed.

187
00:23:03.833 --> 00:23:05.333
what the photographer chooses to reveal.

188
00:23:05.708 --> 00:23:07.166
and what to conceal.

189
00:23:08.708 --> 00:23:11.166
Your perspective is critical.

190
00:23:24.458 --> 00:23:27.583
SPECIAL SCOOP: SPIRIT PICTURES

191
00:23:39.666 --> 00:23:41.250
Hey. Jane. You're early.

192
00:23:43.291 --> 00:23:45.083
I'll get it.

193
00:23:50.583 --> 00:23:52.291
-Hello?
-Hello. Tun.

194
00:23:52.375 --> 00:23:54.666
It's me. Jane.
I'll come by in the afternoon.

195
00:23:55.916 --> 00:23:56.833
Hello?

196
00:23:56.958 --> 00:23:59.166
Tun. can you hear me?

197
00:23:59.791 --> 00:24:00.750
Hello?

198
00:24:00.916 --> 00:24:01.875
Tun!

199
00:24:02.416 --> 00:24:03.375
Tun!

200
00:24:03.666 --> 00:24:04.708
Hello?

201
00:24:05.875 --> 00:24:06.833
Hello?

202
00:24:35.750 --> 00:24:37.083
What's wrong?

203
00:24:37.958 --> 00:24:38.958
I don't know.

204
00:24:39.125 --> 00:24:41.500
My neck has been hurting
since the accident.

205
00:24:42.416 --> 00:24:44.208
You should go see a doctor.

206
00:24:45.958 --> 00:24:47.416
I'm sure it's nothing serious.

207
00:24:51.041 --> 00:24:52.750
What's the use of talking to these quacks?

208
00:24:54.208 --> 00:24:57.500
REAL GHOSTS. DEADLY SPIRIT.
GHOST STORIES. GHOST PATH

209
00:24:59.791 --> 00:25:01.041
Are you a reporter?

210
00:25:01.333 --> 00:25:02.250
No.

211
00:25:03.708 --> 00:25:06.125
The funeral foundation told us
to come here.

212
00:25:08.625 --> 00:25:10.750
We run a legal operation here.

213
00:25:11.333 --> 00:25:12.791
We have all the permits.

214
00:26:02.291 --> 00:26:03.583
Excuse me.

215
00:26:03.958 --> 00:26:06.583
Are all these pictures fake?

216
00:26:07.958 --> 00:26:10.416
Piak. Go tell our boss he has guests.

217
00:26:13.583 --> 00:26:14.750
Everyone fakes them.

218
00:26:16.458 --> 00:26:17.291
You know.

219
00:26:17.708 --> 00:26:19.666
those photos are always a hit.

220
00:26:21.083 --> 00:26:22.833
Any issues with them sell out.

221
00:26:24.208 --> 00:26:25.041
Do you think...

222
00:26:25.625 --> 00:26:27.541
we can always find real ones?

223
00:26:29.166 --> 00:26:31.833
Isn't that deceiving the public?

224
00:26:33.541 --> 00:26:35.250
Our readers...

225
00:26:36.041 --> 00:26:37.791
want to see scary photos.

226
00:26:39.416 --> 00:26:41.125
They don't want love stories.

227
00:26:42.875 --> 00:26:46.416
Does that mean
all the published photos are fake?

228
00:26:49.625 --> 00:26:51.083
I didn't say that.

229
00:27:05.583 --> 00:27:06.458
Take a look.

230
00:27:07.666 --> 00:27:08.666
Do you see anything?

231
00:27:09.875 --> 00:27:12.166
This is the first photo I had.

232
00:27:13.500 --> 00:27:14.875
I took it at home.

233
00:27:16.916 --> 00:27:18.166
People say the shadow in the back

234
00:27:18.375 --> 00:27:20.666
bears an uncanny resemblance to my mom.

235
00:27:24.416 --> 00:27:26.208
Believe what you will.

236
00:27:28.458 --> 00:27:29.583
But this picture...

237
00:27:30.625 --> 00:27:33.000
was taken years after my mom passed away.

238
00:27:35.583 --> 00:27:36.583
You know.

239
00:27:37.166 --> 00:27:38.125
sometimes

240
00:27:38.458 --> 00:27:40.875
spirits just want to be close
to their loved ones.

241
00:27:47.541 --> 00:27:48.958
The pictures that you see.

242
00:27:49.875 --> 00:27:51.083
for me.

243
00:27:52.416 --> 00:27:53.791
are more than just...

244
00:27:54.541 --> 00:27:56.583
pictures with strange shadows in them.

245
00:27:59.000 --> 00:28:00.875
It's the stories behind the pictures.

246
00:28:06.041 --> 00:28:07.208
Think about it.

247
00:28:08.750 --> 00:28:10.125
Why would the dead...

248
00:28:11.208 --> 00:28:12.583
return to the living...

249
00:28:16.333 --> 00:28:19.083
if they are not trying
to tell us something?

250
00:28:23.750 --> 00:28:24.833
Most importantly.

251
00:28:26.166 --> 00:28:27.416
people also believe

252
00:28:28.708 --> 00:28:29.875
that there are connections...

253
00:28:30.958 --> 00:28:33.458
between the shadows
and someone in the picture.

254
00:28:37.750 --> 00:28:38.958
A father.

255
00:28:39.625 --> 00:28:40.541
A mother.

256
00:28:41.125 --> 00:28:42.375
A lover.

257
00:28:44.666 --> 00:28:45.791
Or it could be someone

258
00:28:45.875 --> 00:28:47.958
whom you've wronged in the past.

259
00:29:12.291 --> 00:29:15.000
How can we be sure
those photos aren't just bad exposures

260
00:29:15.166 --> 00:29:16.333
or were forged?

261
00:29:17.166 --> 00:29:19.708
What do you think about polaroids?

262
00:29:23.750 --> 00:29:24.791
Can you forge them?

263
00:29:25.958 --> 00:29:28.083
You load the film cartridge in.
press the shutter.

264
00:29:28.666 --> 00:29:30.125
And out comes the photo.

265
00:29:48.666 --> 00:29:50.041
Tell me. then.

266
00:29:51.291 --> 00:29:52.791
How can they be faked?

267
00:29:57.416 --> 00:29:59.875
How do we know what they want?

268
00:30:00.833 --> 00:30:03.666
Perhaps the answer is in the photo.

269
00:30:14.708 --> 00:30:16.583
Here's the last two shots.

270
00:30:17.625 --> 00:30:18.875
Big smiles.

271
00:30:22.458 --> 00:30:25.541
Can you change your pose for me?

272
00:30:26.125 --> 00:30:29.166
Embrace her. hold the bouquet

273
00:30:29.250 --> 00:30:31.416
and put your cheeks close together.

274
00:30:32.958 --> 00:30:33.958
Good.

275
00:30:34.041 --> 00:30:35.166
Beautiful.

276
00:30:37.041 --> 00:30:38.916
We're done. Thank you.

277
00:30:39.000 --> 00:30:41.791
Thank you to you both.

278
00:30:42.250 --> 00:30:44.500
Take them to the dressing room.

279
00:31:10.750 --> 00:31:12.208
What the hell?

280
00:31:14.000 --> 00:31:15.416
Who's doing that?

281
00:31:16.166 --> 00:31:17.583
Aum. check the fuse!

282
